name: INDONESIAN EMBASSY MADRID
text:
1. Morning tweeps! @Menlu_RI #FMMarsudi is currently in Achit Al-Qusayr, Southern of Lebanon to visit Indonesian peacekeepers deployed under the United Nations Interim Force in Lebanon (UNIFIL), Indonesian Battalion (Indobatt) 
#Indonesia4UNSC #ATruePartner4Peace #LebanonVisit

name: INDONESIAN EMBASSY MADRID
text:
2. Prior to her arrival in Indobatt, #FMMarsudi visited the Taybeh Village to inspect the regular medical services provided by the #KontingenGaruda to the local community in Taybeh. Her visit to Taybeh was received w/ warm welcome
#Indonesia4UNSC #ATruePartner4Peace #LebanonVisit

name: INDONESIAN EMBASSY MADRID
text:
3. #FMMarsudi’s arrival in Indobatt was greeted by the traditional pasembahan dance by the female peackeepers of #UNIFIL #Indobatt. The marching band of the #KontingenGaruda also welcomed her from the gate to the #LapanganSoekarno. 
#Indonesia4UNSC #ATruePartner4Peace

name: INDONESIAN EMBASSY MADRID
text:
4. #FMMarsudi  also had the chance to inspect and ride the #Anoa, the #UNIFIL tactical vehicle, along the way to #LapanganSoekarno. #Anoa is the product of Pindad, Indonesia, with finest quality for #Peacekeeping missions
#Indonesia4UNSC #ATruePartner4Peace #LebanonVisit

name: INDONESIAN EMBASSY MADRID
text:
5. During her ceremonious journey to the #LapanganSoekarno, #FMMarsudi was accompanied by the Commander of #KontingenGaruda #UNIFIL, Colonel Infantry Murbianto A. Wibowo & Indonesian Ambassador to Lebanon @KBRIBeirut
#Indonesia4UNSC #ATruePartner4Peace #LebanonVisit

name: INDONESIAN EMBASSY MADRID
text:
6. Commander of #KontingenGaruda officially welcomed #FMMarsudi & expresses his appreciation to her visit. He noted that #FMMarsudi is the first #Menlu that visit #Indobatt #UNIFIL in last 10 years.
#Indonesia4UNSC #ATruePartner4Peace #LebanonVisit

name: INDONESIAN EMBASSY MADRID
text:
7. #FMMarsudi thanked the hundreds of #KontingenGaruda for their service as part of Indonesia’s concrete contribution to maintain peace & stability in Middle East & the world.  
#Indonesia4UNSC #ATruePartner4Peace #LebanonVisit

name: INDONESIAN EMBASSY MADRID
text:
8. Indonesia is proud to have our finest men & women contributed to the global peace & security in #KontingenGaruda. Indonesian peacekeepers have performed excellently & managed to win the trust & supports from the locals. 
#Indonesia4UNSC #ATruePartner4Peace #LebanonVisit

name: INDONESIAN EMBASSY MADRID
text:
9. #FMMarsudi also pleased to witness the increasing number of Indonesian female peacekeepers in #KontingenGaruda from 2018-2017. The female peacekeepers in #UN #Peacekeeping Missions is important to engage & empower the local community
#Indonesia4UNSC #ATruePartner4Peace

name: INDONESIAN EMBASSY MADRID
text:
10.She also had an intense dialogue with numerous Indonesian female peacekeepers to discuss further efforts in promoting more deployment of female peacekeepers to #UN #Peacekeeping Missions
#Indonesia4UNSC #ATruePartner4Peace #LebanonVisit

name: INDONESIAN EMBASSY MADRID
text:
11. Her visit to #Indobatt is a firm commitment of Indonesian government to the world peace & security. #KontingenGaruda in #UNIFIL is the largest contingent of Indonesian peacekeepers with 1.290 total personnels. 
#Indonesia4UNSC #ATruePartner4Peace #LebanonVisit

name: INDONESIAN EMBASSY MADRID
text:
12.Indonesia’s concrete commitment & contribution to the peace & security since 1957 is the milestones achievements that strengthen Indonesia's campaign as the Non-permanent member of the #UN #SecurityCouncil for 2019-2020
#Indonesia4UNSC #ATruePartner4Peace #LebanonVisit

name: INDONESIAN EMBASSY MADRID
text: 1. MoFA RI organized a Panel Discussion on Indonesia’s Candidature as a Non-Permanent Member of the UN Security Council for 2019-2020. It is part of the Working Meeting week for Indonesia’s Heads of Missions in Jakarta, last week. #Indonesia4UNSC #ATruePartner4Peace https://t.co/qwj0tkUvT8

name: INDONESIAN EMBASSY MADRID
text: 2. The distinguished panelists were Hassan Wirajuda, Marty Natalegawa, Dian T. Djani, and Hasan Kleib. The discussion centered on the strengthening of Indonesia’s preparation and sharing of experience and best practices. #Indonesia4UNSC #ATruePartner4Peace https://t.co/AhY5wppERz

name: INDONESIAN EMBASSY MADRID
text: 3. Hassan Wirajuda underlined the importance of maintaining Indonesia’s principle of firm in stance but flexible in approach. The principle is one of Indonesia’s key merits in pursuing its aspiration to once again become the member of UNSC. #Indonesia4UNSC #ATruePartner4Peace

name: INDONESIAN EMBASSY MADRID
text: 4. Marty Natalegawa conveyed his view that regionalism shall be an integral part in Indonesia’s aspiration during its membership. To be able to leave a regional footprint will be amongst Indonesia’s notable achievements. #Indonesia4UNSC #ATruePartner4Peace

name: INDONESIAN EMBASSY MADRID
text: 5. @DTDjani emphasized on Indonesia’s credentials and track-record in the last 60 years in contributing to the UN Peacekeeping missions around the world. It shall serve as a reminder of Indonesia’s commitment to the purposes of the UNSC. #Indonesia4UNSC #ATruePartner4Peace

name: INDONESIAN EMBASSY MADRID
text: 6. Hassan Kleib said Indonesia shall prepare its candidature comprehensively including on the understanding of technical aspects. Indonesia looks forward to continue contributing to issues of common concern with its vast and rich experiences. #Indonesia4UNSC #ATruePartner4Peace

name: INDONESIAN EMBASSY MADRID
text: 7. The dynamic nature of the current world’s architecture could potentially present unprecedented challenges for many countries including Indonesia. Therefore, Indonesia’s experience as bridge-builder and mediator are of crucial modalities. #Indonesia4UNSC #ATruePartner4Peace

name: INDONESIAN EMBASSY MADRID
text: 8. As a politically stable, economically strong, and a law-abiding nation, Indonesia shall be a true partner to create an ecosystem of peace to achieve sustainable development as well as in combating terrorism and radicalization. #Indonesia4UNSC #ATruePartner4Peace https://t.co/Ht7ykTfVF8

name: INDONESIAN EMBASSY MADRID
text: 9. For Indonesia, creating an ecosystem of peace, stability, and prosperity should start at home. Indonesia is a living proof that democracy and Islam can co-exist peacefully and harmoniously based on the principle of religious freedom and tolerance. #Indonesia4UNSC https://t.co/TSamjOH9ZL

name: INDONESIAN EMBASSY MADRID
text: 10. The forum recalled Indonesia’s Minister for Foreign Affairs’ message that the membership in the UNSC is not about how big or small a country is, rather, a country’s track-record and commitment to contribute to world peace needs to be assured. #Indonesia4UNSC https://t.co/8VobIS6hab
